Subject: [PATCH] config/override.m4: drop strict autoconf 2.69 version check

newlib ships a Cygnus-era config/override.m4 that asserts the host's
autoconf is _exactly_ 2.69 via _GCC_AUTOCONF_VERSION_CHECK.  On modern
distros (CachyOS / Arch ship autoconf 2.73, Fedora 41 ships 2.72, etc.)
running `autoreconf -fi` fails with

    configure.ac: error: Please use exactly Autoconf 2.69 instead of 2.73.

We run autoreconf on newlib during the PPU toolchain build so that the
patches which add a new sys_dir (patches 0001/0004, `lv2`) actually
propagate into the pregenerated configure + Makefile.in.  Pinning to
2.69 would require every builder to install a parallel legacy autoconf
— or for us to ship hand-patched 30k-line generated files — neither of
which is worth the bother for a consumer-grade ABI target.

Replace the strict-equality check with a no-op.  The overridden macros
earlier in override.m4 are all backports of Autoconf-newer macros into
older versions; they continue to work unchanged under newer autoconf,
they're just shadowed by the already-present versions.  Modern autoconf
output has been verified to produce a working configure + Makefile.in
for the combined GCC+newlib tree on this target.

diff --git a/config/override.m4 b/config/override.m4
--- a/config/override.m4
+++ b/config/override.m4
@@ -39,10 +39,8 @@ dnl   m4_define([_GCC_AUTOCONF_VERSION], [X.Y])
 dnl in configure.ac before AC_INIT,
 dnl without rewriting this file.
 dnl Or for updating the whole tree at once with the definition above.
-AC_DEFUN([_GCC_AUTOCONF_VERSION_CHECK],
-[m4_if(m4_defn([_GCC_AUTOCONF_VERSION]),
-  m4_defn([m4_PACKAGE_VERSION]), [],
-  [m4_fatal([Please use exactly Autoconf ]_GCC_AUTOCONF_VERSION[ instead of ]m4_defn([m4_PACKAGE_VERSION])[.])])
-])
+dnl PS3 toolchain: strict-version check dropped so modern autoconf
+dnl (2.70+) can regenerate newlib's configure after patches land.
+AC_DEFUN([_GCC_AUTOCONF_VERSION_CHECK], [])
 m4_define([AC_INIT], m4_defn([AC_INIT])[
 _GCC_AUTOCONF_VERSION_CHECK
 ])
